description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you a Health Care Assistant looking for a rewarding role? You’ll find a friendly welcome and a home for your talents at Practice Plus Group. Whether you’re coming from an NHS or private hospital or another care setting, we’ll give you time to use your skills – and help you build a fulfilling career.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are looking to join an energetic and vibrant organisation that truly makes a difference to people’s lives on a daily basis we would like to hear from you. We are looking for a Health Care Assistant to join our team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be a valued member of our Outpatient team supported by our experienced Manager, Ewa. As a Health Care Assistant you will not only support the nursing staff; you will also participate in the pre-assessment of patients, undertaking basic tests and investigations under supervision. This will include vital signs recording, venepuncture, ECG recordings, urinalysis and peak flow recordings.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have completed your NVQ Level 3 in Health and Social Care or be willing to work towards it and hold your BLS certificate. With recent experience working as a Health Care Assistant in an acute setting it would be advantageous if you have performed basic investigations but it is not essential. Above all, you have a natural ability to help make the lives of others more fulfilling, the ability to follow instructions and prioritise a busy workload and the desire to work in an environment where the work can be hard, but also fun and rewarding.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Working at Practice Plus Group&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Everything we do is focused on providing a high standard of safe and effective patient care. Our facilities are modern, employing the latest technology with friendly and professional staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We want our team members to feel motivated and rewarded. So we offer a competitive package of pay and benefits. We also recognise the value of a healthy work-life balance – so we always try to be flexible, helping you fit your working life around your home life.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To apply for the role click on the link below. If you have any questions contact Sonia Sanghviin our friendly resourcing team, or call 07580 018971.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We will contact all shortlisted candidate but please note Practice Plus Group retain the right to remove the advert prior to the closing date if a suitable candidate is appointed. Our employment offers are subject to receipt of satisfactory pre-employment checks. At Practice Plus Group, we actively promote diversity and equal opportunities. Applicants must have the right to work in the EU.&lt;/p&gt;
